commit.message:
Handle windows closing gracefully under X11 (#42)

Request and process WM_DELETE_WINDOW events, so that clicking on the "close"
button is equivalent to calling `Graphics.close_graph`.  Subsequent graphical
operations will raise the `Graphic_failure` exception instead of killing
the program on an I/O error.

In passing, use `XPending` + `XNextEvent` instead of `XCheckMaskEvent(-1)`,
as the latter ignores client events such as WM_DELETE_WINDOW.

Co-authored-by: David Allsopp <david.allsopp@metastack.com>

commit.message:
Increase default size to 1024x768

For consistency with the Windows port, and because we have bigger
screens these days.

Resurrect the "sorts" example

- Add a synchronization barrier on comparisons so that the various sorts
  execute in lock-step and their efficiency can be visually compared.
- Reinstall the adjustable delay so that it runs at human speeds.
- Terminate all threads cleanly.
- Add heap sort back.
